citations:
    citation-agot-daenerys-vii:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Daenerys VII"
            text_from_source: "I will take my khalasar west to where the world ends, and ride the wooden horses across the black salt water as no khal has done before. I will kill the men in the iron suits and tear down their stone houses … This I vow, I, Drogo son of Bharbo."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "A wine merchant (sent by King Robert, acting on Magister Illyrio's letter) attempts to poison Daenerys with a cask of Arbor wine. Ser Jorah Mormont intervenes. Drogo swears a great oath before the Mother of Mountains to invade the Seven Kingdoms and win the Iron Throne for Rhaego, the unborn son. The khalasar departs Vaes Dothrak, heading southwest. The poisoner is chained to Dany's silver and forced to run after it. Dany places the dragon eggs in a brazier — they do not hatch, but glow. Robert Baratheon is confirmed as having offered lordships for Daenerys's death."
